<br>
When inside a dungeon with mobs above and below me, I have been only casting single target stuns, but never the color stun line of spells. This is because I have always been told that if I use an AoE spell in a dungeon, I will pull the mobs surrounding me, above me, and below me onto my group. However, is this the case with such a small AoE as the color stun line of spells? <br>
<br>
Suppose I were in Velks Lab when higher level, and I am in the pit, or the false wall. What, as professional and high level enchanters, do you all do in a situation like that? <br>
<br>
I appreciate any input concerning my question and would like to thank those that respond in advance! =)<br>
<br>
-Zamb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camehleon>CamehLeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#330000>(12/9/02 5:42:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ifrance.com/camehlheon/images/camehbourre.gif width=129 height=91></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> Hello,<br>
the only time I got this kinda problem was in CoM (I was lvl 35 or so...) and I aggroed a goo that was passing by behind me.<br>
<br>
I never had problems using AoE stuns in dungeons (in velks, etc)<br>
<br>
It won't go through the floor or the roof, don't worry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just ensure there ain't no unwanted NPC within your Stun range, and it will be fine.<br>
<br>
Good Luck <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10374><img src="http://www.morosa.f9.co.uk/cameh.jpg"></a> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skylaamacleod>SkylaaMacLeod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#330000>(12/9/02 1:27:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> I've not had a problem using any of my AoE mezzes or stuns.    I did alot of hunting in Lguk, CoM, Velks, SolB and SSRA.  I actually prefer using the AoE mezzes for those monks that like to pull 6 mobs to the group and then FD at our feet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(12/10/02 12:49:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> <br>
AE stuns and mezzes are high risk, high reward things.  Resists can kill you at the higher levels, so using them is a calculated effort.  One problem with AE mezz for example, is that its level limited and the Mob you would like to mezz most just likely just aggroed on you.<br>
<br>
These spells have their place, in particular in lower level chanters, but have a more restricted usage as time goes on.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 59 Chanter - Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skylaamacleod>SkylaaMacLeod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#330000>(12/10/02 6:15:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> At the 59th level, I mostly use my AoE mezz, Fascination in PoN, on the trigger spider spawn.  I'm not sure the level limit on that but I haven't reached it there yet on the spiders.  I also use it in the basement in SSRA on the skeles quite a bit.  I don't get many resist.<br>
<br>
I try to keep GRM up too so that I don't mezz myself. In open areas, about the only time I mezz myself is when I'm mid cast and someone gets aggro and runs over to me.   In dugeons, I've noticed if I get mezzed, my mezz wears off with just about enough time to cast one of the color lines, then I can start the mezz process over again or I'll get a resist and that mob will hit me breaking my mezz, then I can start the mezz process again.  I can't recall anytime dying because I was mezzed and couldn't get the situation under control.  <br>
<br>
I've had a ton of fun with the AoE mezzes.  Now that single target mezzes can overwrite it, I find it even more valuable.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lyanne>Lyanne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(12/12/02 1:48:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> I stopped using aoe stuns in dungeon areas after pulling things from rooms on other side of the wall in SolA.  I figure if the hallways aren't very wide, it shouldn't be used, if wide enough that hopefully things are out of range in a dungeon environment, I use it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125874"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">Lyanne Windrider Lvl 51 fletching Druid</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381516"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;">Mayyne BattleSmith Lvl 31 Enchantress and Armor/Weapons Pimp</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=463336"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Nillas Traynemaker AKA 'The Toy'</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deltoran>Deltoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(12/17/02 8:33:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> Had that problem in Unrest, Mistmore, one or two rooms in Paw, the Sarn Fortress LOIO,.... and a couple others.  I like to run a test before actually fighting an area.  I bind outside the zoneline, if it gets really messy as I walk thru and cast my stuns, I watch for adds from other rooms and levels, gate as needed. Actually I have found it can be a nice way to pull mobs from diff levels above and below, if you know they are coming.  Other than that Explore your dungeon, if it is extreemly close quarters then avoid using it.  If you have long open hallways and tunnels by all means it is a life saver.<br>
Good Luck<br>
